description:
**Hitapps** is a GameDev company specializing in two areas: Hybrid-casual & Casual (Puzzle/Brain Teasers). We have several successful products in both categories with a combined total of over 80 000 000 downloads, and we are currently featured in the top charts in the Games section. We adhere to principles of openness and transparency, and we are results-oriented while valuing work-life balance.


We are currently searching for a talented **Game Designer** to join our Casual team. In this role, you will be working on new projects and supporting existing successful ones.  



**Responsibilities:*** Designing game mechanics and UX within the product;
* Analyzing product metrics and developing hypotheses;
* Creating and balancing the sequence of levels;
* Maintaining design documentation;
* Collaborating with the development team.

**Why you?*** Minimum 3 years of experience in the Gamedev industry;
* Experience working on LiveOps projects;
* Experience in level balancing and designing game systems in projects;
* Understanding of typical game mechanics;
* Ability to structure information and express thoughts clearly and convincingly (both orally and in writing);
* Analytical mindset and a good grasp of logic;
* A deep passion for games.

**Why us?*** Official employment;
* High salary level;
* Medical insurance;
* 100% compensation for vacations, sick leave, and day-offs;
* Compensation for educational and sports activities;
* Work in a team without bureaucracy;
* Opportunity to influence processes within the department.

**Let's create hits together!**

**Hitapps** is a GameDev company specializing in two areas: Hybrid-casual & Casual (Puzzle/Brain Teasers). We have several successful products in both categories with a combined total of over 80 000 000 downloads, and we are currently featured in the top charts in the Games section. We adhere to principles of openness and transparency, and we are results-oriented while valuing work-life balance.  



**Hitapps** is in search of a **Creative Producer** whom we confidently entrust with the task of working on creative videos for our products.  



**Responsibilities:**  

* Independently develop concepts and write technical briefs for various channels, generate new ideas and hypotheses;
* Interpret key business indicators and make informed conclusions regarding product performance and development;
* Test and adapt hypotheses for UA creatives, continuously study the target audience;
* Detail scenarios and collaborate with video production teams;
* Track trends and analyze the visual aspects of the market (via Sensor Tower/App Annie).

**Why you?**  

* Relevant work experience in similar positions for at least 2 years in the game development industry;
* Experience with major sources in paid social and advertising networks is welcomed;
* Project management skills and advanced communication abilities;
* Analytics experience;
* Playable experience;
* Ability to analyze statistical data, articulate risks, and set priorities correctly.

**Why us?**  

* Official employment;
* High salary level tied to the dollar;
* Medical insurance;
* 100% compensation for vacations/sick leave/day offs;
* Compensation for training/sports activities;
* Work in a small, bureaucracy-free team;
* Opportunity to influence processes within the department.

**Let's create hits together!**

G5 Games is a game developer and publisher headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden. We have over 900+ talented professionals worldwide who work remotely in one of our 10 locations. More than 20 years ago, the company became one of the first mobile game developers in the world.


You may know us from hit projects like Sherlock, Hidden City®, Mahjong Journey®, The Secret Society®, the Jewels series, and many others.


We are currently looking for a talented Writer/Screenwriter to join our team.


What you will work on:


* Write texts, scripts, and dialogues flawlessly, engagingly, and concisely;
* Create and describe quest chains: mysteries, intrigues, investigations;
* Conceptualize and describe the game world, locations, and characters;
* Work in a team only.

It’s important to us:


* Experience in writing game texts and scripts;
* Love for games and extensive gaming experience;
* Understanding of the game development process and the specifics of game scripts;
* Ability to clearly and competently express your thoughts in Russian;
* Creativity;
* Logical thinking.

Would be a great bonus:


* Experience in journalism/copywriting/game design;
* Higher education in the field of linguistics, philology, journalism;
* Knowledge of the English.

Working at G5 is about:


* The opportunity to bring your ideas to life in an international company with a multimillion audience: G5 games are played by 250 million users worldwide.
* Official employment in one of our locations or remotely under a contract in countries where the company doesn't have offices.
* Assistance with relocation that helps move to one of the countries where the company has offices: Armenia, Georgia, Kazakhstan or Montenegro.
* Maintaining a work-life balance of employees: remote work and flexible hours, sports reimbursement, and health insurance payment.
* Charitable activities: you can initiate your own project with the company's support or participate in G5 Charity events.
* Opportunities for professional development: access to resources for creating your own projects within R&D, an internal educational platform, and training webinars covering various specialties.
* Bonus system: project profit bonus for project teams and a performance share program for key employees.
* Language courses: free English lessons, speaking clubs for all proficiency levels, and free study language of the country of relocation.
* Entertainment: corporate events and team buildings, master classes for adults and children, webinars with guest speakers, coffee talks, quizzes, and contests.

Please be aware that the email correspondence with G5 Games representatives is conducted via g5.com only.

